    "body": "> > I want to grant multiple roles to multiple users.\r\n> \r\n> This is already possible with the current contract. Can you elaborate the benefits you see from organizing roles as ERC1155?\r\n\r\nA significant benefit of this would be that we embrace having access to network-level permissions rather than contract-level permissions established by an organization/protocol/etc. With 1155-driven access, people can more effectively manage the permissions across the entire network without running a function on every piece deployed or having to \"use the chain as a database.\"\r\n\r\nFor reference, here is an example of `AccessControl` built using ERC1155 badges: https://github.com/nftchance/remus/blob/master/contracts/auth/BadgeAccessControl.sol\r\n\r\nAlthough the logic for minting/revoking Badges has been excluded, it makes sense for that to be the case as localizing the minting of the Badges would negate the benefits when aiming to create network-level permission systems.",
